
Steps:
1) Create new Maven project
2) Update pom.xml
3) Create folder structure
4) Create page object class for login screen
5) Create base class
6) create Login test case
7) See integration of Config.properties, ReadConfig.java and Base Class
8) Add logs to test case
9) Read common values from properties file
9) Run test case on desired browser
10)Add extent report
10)Create Data Driven test case
10)Adding new test case


Read common values from Config.properties file:
1) Config.properties
2) ReadConfig.java
3) Base Class


Maven ---> pom.xml
Download dependencies from mvnrepository.com

log4j  ----> log4j.jar in pom.xml
log4j.properties ---> 

Add extent report:
1) Extent report Jars ---> in pom.xml
2) extent-config.xml ----> in Home directory
3) Listener class (Reporting.java) ---> Utility file
4) Add entry in Testng.xml file (<Listener>)

System.getProperty("user.dir") ----> Only in java classes
./  ---> in java classes & in properties


Run Test case on desired browser
1) Code in Base Class
2) Code in Testng.xml


Data Driven Test Case (For example read data from xlsx file) : 
1) Apache Poi jar 
2) Apache Poi - ooxml to read xls file
3) XLS or XLSX file 
4) XLUtils.java



New Test Case
1) Page Object Class
